Class jsonElement

java.lang.Object
jsonElement
Direct Known Subclasses:
jsonComplexElement
public class jsonElement extends Object
Holds information about primitive jsonElements. Primitive jsonElements are string, integer, boolean, and null values. Information stored about the elements includes (1) name if the element has one, (2) type of element, (3) depth of element, (4) element value, (5) element parent.

  • Field Details

    • name

      protected String name
      Name of the jsonElement. It will be set to "" if the element is anonymous.

    • typeName

      protected String typeName
      typeName of the element. Represented as a string, for example, "string" or "boolean".

    • depth

      protected int depth
      Depth within the abstract syntax tree that the element is positioned at.

    • value

      protected String value
      Value of the jsonElement.

    • parent

      protected jsonComplexElement parent
      Direct parent element of the jsonElement. This will either be a jsonObject or jsonArray.
